data.description: This quality built home was built in 1994 by an amish construction crew. When walking up you are greeted with a wide, length of house, cement front porch. Through the front door, an elegant two story foyer open to the second floor balcony. Instantly you notice the amount of oak trim and solid oak doors throughout the whole house. When walking on tour take notice to the solid floors constructed of 2x6 oak boards laid on rough cut oak 2x12 joist first and second floor. The walls even have oak 2x4 boards. On left of foyer, a spacious office. On right right of foyer, an extra long cozy family room. Proceeding on left you will find a good size half bath. The house then opens up into a kitchen with an island, an eat in dinning and walk-out patio doors. Walking upstairs you will see a master suite on one side of house, and two bedrooms on the other side of the foyer with another full bath in the middle of the hall way. When entering the master bedroom you are greeted with an abundance of natural light and space. Continuing into the master bath, there again is an abundance of light and space with a two person garden tub, a walk in shower, and two tall storage cabinets. Attached is a walk-in closet with washer and dryer. Basement includes full cold storage under the front porch, and a walk out man door into the garage, which has 9 ft insulated garage doors. Around the back a large cement pad for parking, large deck with hot tub and above ground pool. Home warranty included
